mdElement.text: We draw it as Movie containing docs. But our stereotypes turn it around: Movie's relationship to docs is EXCLUDED. Doc refers to movie by FK. This is the toolkit's "logical yet physical" approach.

How this gets mapped by toolkit: Movie contains array of Role. MovieContributor contains array of Role. Role, drawn here as an association class, is mapped to an ES entity. Besides the three attribs shown here, toolkit add references to Movie and MovieContributor, either as contained doc or FKs. In this case they are FKs because that's how the association roles are stereotyped.
